    • Method Detail

      • createSchedule

        public static Object createSchedule(spark.Request request,
                                    spark.Response response)
                             throws IOException
        PUT /:user/lambda/:name/schedule/:event-name

        Creates a new scheduled event. The request must contain the name of an existing lambda. Responds with an empty JSON object on success.

        Body parameters
        Name Type Description Required
        calendar string A cron-style timestamp Yes
        parameters object An arbitrary JSON object with parameters to pass to the lambda Yes
        Throws:
        NotAuthenticatedException - 401 Thrown when user is not properly authenticated
        InsufficientPermissionsException - 403 Thrown when the currently authenticated key is not permitted to schedule events on the lambda
        UserNotFoundException - 404 Thrown when target lambda owner is unknown
        LambdaNotFoundException - 404 Thrown when target lambda is unknown
        IOException

      • updateSchedule

        public static Object updateSchedule(spark.Request request,
                                    spark.Response response)
                             throws IOException
        PATCH /:user/lambda/:name/schedule/:event-name

        Updates an existing scheduled event. The request must contain the name of an existing lambda and schedule. Responds with an empty JSON object on success.

        Body parameters
        Name Type Description Required
        calendar string A cron-style timestamp No
        parameters object An arbitrary JSON object with parameters to pass to the lambda No
        Throws:
        NotAuthenticatedException - 401 Thrown when user is not properly authenticated
        InsufficientPermissionsException - 403 Thrown when the currently authenticated key is not permitted to schedule events on the lambda
        UserNotFoundException - 404 Thrown when target lambda owner is unknown
        LambdaNotFoundException - 404 Thrown when target lambda is unknown
        IOException

      • readSchedule

        public static Object readSchedule(spark.Request request,
                                  spark.Response response)
        GET /:user/lambda/:name/schedule/:event-name

        Reads information about an existing scheduled event. No body parameters are required. The request must contain the name of an existing lambda and schedule.

        Response values
        Name Type Description
        calendar string Execution timestamp
        parameters object JSON parameter object passed to the lambda
        Throws:
        NotAuthenticatedException - 401 Thrown when user is not properly authenticated
        InsufficientPermissionsException - 403 Thrown when the currently authenticated key is not permitted to read scheduled events of the lambda
        UserNotFoundException - 404 Thrown when target lambda owner is unknown
        LambdaNotFoundException - 404 Thrown when target lambda is unknown

      • deleteSchedule

        public static Object deleteSchedule(spark.Request request,
                                    spark.Response response)
        DELETE /:user/lambda/:name/schedule/:event-name

        Deletes an existing scheduled event. The request must contain the name of an existing lambda and schedule. Responds with an empty JSON object on success.

        Throws:
        NotAuthenticatedException - 401 Thrown when user is not properly authenticated
        InsufficientPermissionsException - 403 Thrown when the currently authenticated key is not permitted to delete scheduled events of the lambda
        UserNotFoundException - 404 Thrown when target lambda owner is unknown
        LambdaNotFoundException - 404 Thrown when target lambda is unknown

      • getScheduledEvents

        public static Object getScheduledEvents(spark.Request request,
                                        spark.Response response)
        GET /:user/lambda/:name/schedules

        Lists existing scheduled events of a lambda. The request must contain the name of an existing lambda.

        Response values
        Name Type Description
        name string Scheduled event name
        calendar string A cron-style timestamp No
        parameters object An arbitrary JSON object with parameters to pass to the lambda No
        Throws:
        NotAuthenticatedException - 401 Thrown when user is not properly authenticated
        InsufficientPermissionsException - 403 Thrown when the currently authenticated key is not permitted to read scheduled events of the lambda
        UserNotFoundException - 404 Thrown when target lambda owner is unknown
        LambdaNotFoundException - 404 Thrown when target lambda is unknown
